main event: A radar-tracked object was observed visually by observers, but they failed to see the object that was tracked by radar.
interesting points: The object was initially tracked distinctly on radar, but then apparently disappeared from radar after about 2 minutes.
Visual observers failed to see the object that was tracked by radar.
The object was described as ellipse-shaped with a trailing edge that was indistinct and appeared recessed.
The object had numerous fairly large bluish-gray lights on the underside that were bright on the periphery and diminishing toward the center.
The object traveled a smooth path of approximately 215 degrees directly over the heads of the observers for about 4 minutes.
